      <div id="content">
		<h1>Simon Rudkin</h1>
                <img src="pawel/pawel_dlotko.JPG" alt="Simon Rudkin." style="float:right;width:270px;height:500px;">
                I am a Senior Lecturer in Data Science at the University of Manchester affiliated with the Institute of Data Science and Artificial Intelligence and the Department of Social Statistics. Previously I have held positions in Economics at Swansea University, the University of Liverpool and University of Manchester. I obtained my PhD in Economics from the University of Manchester in 2008.

                <br>
                <br>
                My research focuses on the messages in data which are hidden in plain sight. Prior to working with topological data analysis (TDA) my work considered distributional regression and treatment effects. Recent papers apply TDA to analysis of stock returns, credit risk and Brexit voting behaviours. My primary research focus is demonstrating the strengths of TDA within Economics and Finance, establishing the relationships between TDA metrics and understood concepts in the discipline literatures.
                <br>
                


		</p>

